-- module `rdefs` — rename gate (#254 Stage 2) shared definitions. Rename
-- TARGETS are PARAMETER-LESS top-level values (`foo`, `also`): per #913 a click
-- on a function name WITH parameters resolves to the WRONG binder (a param's
-- local-binder def Loc collides with the function name's own Loc), so a rename
-- target must be parameter-less. `foo` carries a TYPE SIGNATURE and is
-- SELECTIVELY imported by rmain, so a COMPLETE rename must rewrite the def, the
-- `foo :` signature, every use, AND the `import …{foo}` clause — all now indexed
-- (refindex.mdk records sig-name + import-clause occurrences, #254 Stage 2).
export foo : Int
foo = 10

export also : Int
also = foo + 1
